Police are appealing for information following an arson attack at a residential property in Lisburn in the early hours of Friday. Officers were called to the scene in Manor Park about 05:45 BST after two petrol bombs were thrown at the property, causing smoke and damage to the front of the building.The resident of the property was at home at the time, but was unaware of the attack.Police are appealing to anyone with information to come forward. Meanwhile, in Strabane police are at the scene of an ongoing security alert near Bradley Way. The Great Northern Link Road is closed between Lifford Road and Bradley Way roundabouts.  
